### [Psalms Chapter 71](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#001.md)

[Psalms 71:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">psa 71:1</span></span>

The Psalmist, probably in old age, appeals to God for help from his
enemies, pleading his past favors, and stating his present need; and, in
confidence of a hearing, he promises his grateful thanks and praise.
(Psa. 71:1-24)

(Compare [Psa 30:1-3](../../../bib/kjv/psa030.htm#001).md).

[Psalms 71:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">psa 71:3</span></span>

given commandment--literally, "ordained," as in [Psa
44:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa044.htm#004.md); [Psa
68:28](../../../bib/kjv/psa068.htm#028.md).

rock . . . fortress-- ([Psa 18:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa018.htm#002).md).

[Psalms 71:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">psa 71:4</span></span>

cruel man--corrupt and ill-natured--literally, "sour."

[Psalms 71:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">psa 71:5</span></span>

trust--place of trust.

[Psalms 71:6](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">psa 71:6</span></span>

His history from early infancy illustrated God's care, and his wonderful
deliverances were at once occasions of praise and ground of confidence
for the future.

my praise . . . of thee--literally, "in" or "by Thee" ([Psa
22:25](../../../bib/kjv/psa022.htm#025).md).

[Psalms 71:10](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">psa 71:10</span></span>

The craft and malicious taunts of his enemies now led him to call for
aid (compare the terms used, [Sa2
17:12](../../../bib/kjv/sa2017.htm#012.md); [Psa
3:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa003.htm#002.md); [Psa
7:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa007.htm#002).md).

[Psalms 71:12](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#012.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_012">psa 71:12</span></span>

(Compare [Psa 22:19](../../../bib/kjv/psa022.htm#019.md); [Psa
40:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa040.htm#004).md).

[Psalms 71:13](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">psa 71:13</span></span>

(Compare [Psa 35:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa035.htm#004.md); [Psa
40:14](../../../bib/kjv/psa040.htm#014).md).

[Psalms 71:14](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">psa 71:14</span></span>

The ruin of his enemies, as illustrating God's faithfulness, is his
deliverance, and a reason for future confidence.

[Psalms 71:15](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">psa 71:15</span></span>

for I know . . . thereof--innumerable, as he had not time to count them.

[Psalms 71:16](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">psa 71:16</span></span>

in the strength--or, relying on it.

thy righteousness--or, faithful performance of promises to the pious
([Psa 7:17](../../../bib/kjv/psa007.htm#017.md); [Psa
31:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa031.htm#001).md).

[Psalms 71:17](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">psa 71:17</span></span>

Past experience again encourages.

taught me, &c.--by providential dealings.

[Psalms 71:19](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">psa 71:19</span></span>

is very high--distinguished ([Psa
36:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa036.htm#005.md); [Isa
55:9](../../../bib/kjv/isa055.htm#009).md).

[Psalms 71:20](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">psa 71:20</span></span>

depths of the earth--debased, low condition.

[Psalms 71:21](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">psa 71:21</span></span>

increase, &c.--that is, the great things done for me ([Psa
71:19](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#019.md); compare [Psa
40:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa040.htm#005).md).

[Psalms 71:22](../../../bib/kjv/psa071.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">psa 71:22</span></span>

To the occasion of praise he now adds the promise to render it.

will . . . praise--literally, "will thank."

even thy truth--as to Thy truth or faithfulness.

